> i
You are not carrying anything.
> s

> s
You blunder blindly through a forest of coats and frocks until you bump into a solid wall, smacking your forehead against some cold and hard.  Reaching up, your hands caress a smooth, round object protruding from the wall: A doorknob.
> turn doorknob

> turn doorknob
You turn the doorknob and suddenly the door pushes open with a grinding creak.  Light floods into the closet and you can see the world beyond...
> s

> s

You are in a bedroom.
You can see a bed and a pillow.
You can go north or east.
It looks as if no one has used this bedroom in years.  The air is thick with the rank smell of mold and decay. The wooden floorboards are warped and stained, the walls are bare but for the occasional tattered remnants of wallpaper and the bloom of black mold, and the windows are boarded up so tight that you can't see anything between the slats.  A queen-sized bed dominates the western wall. There's a pillow on the bed.  A door to the north leads back into the closet and another to the east leads out to a hallway.

Now that the closet door is open, the light lets you see that the formerly pitch dark closet is full of coats.

This room is familiar.... yet strange.  You're not sure what to make of it.  You rub your button eyes in confusion.  Again you wonder, were you asleep? How was that possible?  Well... that doesn't matter now.  the important thing is that you're awake again now.

Good morning, Poppet.
