You squint at the paper, trying to read the tiny ornate type. It looks like this was once part of a longer book, so the words out of context don't make a lot of sense to you."...much to the surprise of the unwary magus. Such things are often created unwittingly, by people unaware of how the psychic vibrations of their emotions may affect the surroundings. After an intense bout of fear, for instance, do not be astonished to find that your paranoia may have focused upon some object with such force as to give it the semblance of locomotion.  Children are especially suseptible to this form of deep magic and their fears of a noctural bogeyman in the dark may inadvertantly create such a reality, in the form of animating an old coat or some such in the back of the closet. Often it is an easy matter to put such apparitions to rest simply by proving to them that you do not fear them.  Approach the animated coat with an offer to mend patch its threadbare elbows.  Approach the walking mannequin with an offer to oil its rusty joints.  You will find that these simple acts of courage will cause their fearsome "life force" to drain away quickly.  In addition--"It cuts off abruptly as the page ends.
