You are in an office.
You can see a rolltop desk, a swivel chair, a filing cabinet, a figure and a tome.
You can go east.
Polly was forbidden from entering Grandfather's office, so the room has always held a certain sinister fascination for you.  What secrets could lie within that the old man didn't want anyone to know about?  The room is cramped, barely big enough for a battered rolltop desk, a swivel chair, and a dinged metal filing cabinet.  There's a thick book sitting on the desk.

You jolt as you catch sight of a decimated human figure standing in the corner, shrouded in shadows but still gleaming white.
> x figure

> x figure
On second glance, you realize that this isn't a human at all.  It's a medical skeleton, suspended from a wire dangling off a pole on a portable wheeled base.  Its eyeless sockets and rictis grin are unnerving but harmless.

You're not sure why Grandfather would have such a grisly trophy in his office.  Was Grandfather a doctor of some sort?  You wrack your fluff brain trying to remember... You do remember visitors would come frequently, each one impatiently waiting in the foyer for their turn to enter the office and consult with Grandfather.  You're just a doll, though, so it never occurred to you to be curious about that.  Your only concern was Polly and her games. But Grandfather must have been a doctor and those visitors must have been his patients.  That must be the explanation.
> x desk

> x desk
A hefty rolltop desk made of solid oak, full of lots of little drawers.
