You are in a kitchen.
You can see Jingles, Tomas, Pirouette, a pile of china, a sink with cupboard and a muslin tutu.
You can go east or west.
The kitchen is a cramped room, ringed with cabinets and counters. There is a sink in the southern corner, between an ice box and a water heater. The floor is covered with warped checkerboard linoleum.

In contrast to the rest of the house, the kitchen is bustling with activity.  It's such a shock after the silence of the dining room that you have to take a moment to compose yourself. Several toys that you recognize are shuffling about, moving from cabinet to cabinet, chattering all the while as they collect trinkets and baubles.  They seem to be building a large pile of cups and saucers in the center of the room.

You remember these toys well: There's Jingles, the plush elephant.  And Pirouette, the dancing ballerina. And finally Tomas, the baby doll.  You wonder what's got them so excited.
> x pile

> x pile
Jingles, Pirouette, and Tomas are collecting tea cups and saucers from the kitchen's cabinets and stacking them in a pile in the center of the room.  You're not sure why.
> x Jingles

> x Jingles
Jingles is a blue plush elephant with big floppy ears and a long, dragging trunk.  His velvet skin is ragged and patchy and he's lost enough stuffing that he barely resembles a mighty pachyderm anymore.  You remember that he used to have a jingle bell tied to the end of his tail, but that has long since been lost.
> speak to Jingles

> speak to Jingles
"Poppet! You're awake!"  Jingles wags his tail and trumpets happily as you approach. "Juliette said you would be joining us! I'm so happy!"

"Yes," you say.  You stare uncertainly at the growing pile of china in the center of the room. "What's going on here? What are you lot doing?"

"Juliette said we should collect all the tea cups and saucers we could find," says Jingles. "It's very important!"

You stare at the pile dubiously, not sure what to make of it. "Important? But... why?"

Jingles shrugs his big velvet ears. "Dunno.  But Juliette said it's very important if we want to... stay awake.  So we'd better get to it!"
> x Tomas

> x Tomas
Tomas is a baby doll with a large rubber head and hard rubber hands. No legs but the rest of his body is just a fabric bag stuffed with soft cotton.  At one time, his eyes would close by their own accord if you laid him on his back.  But now his left eye is permanently at half-mast, lolling crazily under a semi-closed lid.  His mouth is molded into a permanent O, perfect for a pretend bottle or just his own thumb.
> speak to Tomas

> speak to Tomas
"Poppet? Is Poppet?" squeaks Tomas as you approach.  He drops his tea cup and squeals in delight. "Poppet! Poppet!"

"Hello, Tomas, I'm ever so delighted to see you again!"

"Have you seen Polly? Where is Polly?" asks Tomas.  There's a strange note of panic in his voice, as if he's begging you for reassurance that you've seen Polly.

"I haven't seen Polly, sorry," you say.

"Oh." His face falls.  "Oh."
