> speak to Winston

> speak to Winston
"It's good to see you again, Winston," you say politely.

"Hmmpf," snorts Winston.  He's always been a gruff old bear.  He's one of the oldest toys in the nursery, so he's never brooked much for the playfulness of some of the newer toys. "I see you've woken up too.  About time! I don't cotton to these lazybones newer toys, always sleeping in, never doing an honest day's work."
> ask Winston about Polly

> ask Winston about Polly
"Winston, have you seen Polly since you woke up?" you ask.

Winston laughs harshly. "Of course not, Poppet.  Polly's long since grown up."

Winston chuckles at your horrified expression. "Come off it, Poppet, surely it's obvious? Look at the state of the house and think about how many years must have passed.  I know that Jingles and Tomas refuse to face facts, but you must have figured out the truth."

"How can we be awake if Polly isn't here?" you ask. "No toy can be awake after its girl has grown up..."

"Ah!" Winston taps his nose knowingly. "That's what Juliette's plan is all about.  But just wait.  You'll see."
> ask Winston about Juliette

> ask Winston about Juliette
"I know it must have been pretty scary to wake up and find that Polly's gone," says Winston, "But luckily Juliette's got a plan that will help us all."

"What's this plan?" you ask.

"You'll see soon enough," says Winston. "But suffice to say, you won't need to miss Polly anymore."

"I don't think I could ever not miss Polly!" you say.

Winston snorts.  "We'll see."
> ask Winston about china

> ask Winston about china
"What's with that big pile of china in the kitchen?  Tomas, Jingles and Pirouette are collecting it all for some reason... Looks like they're getting ready for a big teaparty!"

"Ah yes, you might say that," says Winston. "That's all part of Juliette's plan."

"Her plan... to have a tea party?"

"Her plan to make sure that we all get to stay awake!"
> ask Winston about trapdoor

> ask Winston about trapdoor
"What's in the cellar?" you ask. "Can I go down there?"

"It's not time for you to know yet," says Winston. "No one gets past me and I'm standing guard until Juliette tells me otherwise!  But believe me, what's down there will benefit all of us."

"What do you mean?" you ask.

"Well, let me ask you this, Poppet: Do you like being awake?"

"..Yes?"

"Good. So do I."

You wait for Winston to say more, but it looks like that's the end of the conversation.
