In contrast to the rest of the house, the kitchen is bustling with activity.  It's such a shock after the silence of the dining room that you have to take a moment to compose yourself. Several toys that you recognize are shuffling about, moving from cabinet to cabinet, chattering all the while as they collect trinkets and baubles.  They seem to be building a large pile of cups and saucers in the center of the room.

You remember these toys well: There's Jingles, the plush elephant.  And Pirouette, the dancing ballerina. And finally Tomas, the baby doll.  You wonder what's got them so excited.
