You are in a den.
You can see a smoking chair, a fireplace, a bearskin rug, a deer heads and a taxidermy animal.
You can go east.
Polly's Grandfather and guests would often retire to this room after dinner to talk and smoke pipes.  It was unspoken but generally understood that this was a space for men, so Polly rarely came in here.  But sometimes, when Grandfather was out, Polly would sneak in here for the illicit thrill of going into a forbidden place.  It is a cozy room, the walls lined with dark walnut bookshelves and a large plush smoking chair facing a marble fireplace.  A balding bearskin rug is draped before the hearth and taxidermied deer heads gaze down from the walls with their glass eyes.

There is a taxidermied animal here.
> take claw

> take claw
You clamp the pliers around one of the creatures claws and push against it with all your might -- after a grueling minute, you're rewarded with a splintering crack and the claw falls free of the creature's paw.

Your breath catches in your throat momentarily as you suddenly wonder if this might be enough to revive the animal again.  But apparently now.  It remains completely inert.

Satisfied it's not going to bother you, you pocket the loose claw.
> pick up claw

> pick up claw
The animal's claws are real.  Curiously, you tug at a claw on one of its feet, but it's attached too firmly to remove by hand.
